/////////////////////////////////////////
// Install the GCC for building software
// --------------------------------------
//To get GCC on Debian Machines:
//  sudo apt-get install build-essential

//To get GCC on Debian Machines:
//   su -c "yum groupinstall development-tools"

//To get GCC on Windows Boxes:
//   1) http://sourceforge.net/projects/mingw/
//   2) Click Green "Download" Button
//   3) Run MinGW-get-installer; Click Next/Accept Till it Takes
//   4) ­ADD MinGW to PATH!
//      - Press Windows Button + R
//      - Type: "control sysdm.cpl" press enter (Hit UAC Yes if it pops)
//      - Select "Advanced" Tab
//      - Click "Environment Variables" on the bottom right
//      - On the bottom half, System Variables, find PATH; click Edit...
//      - Scroll to the right; add Path to MinGW w/ semicolon (ex: 
;C:\MinGW\bin\ )

